<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1264,1286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1264,1286]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
1. Elytra yellow or pale yellow (
<figureCitation box="[512,585,1264,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,366,1376]" captionTargetId="figure-102@5.[151,1436,345,1400]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Axinoscymnus cardilobus Ren et Pang, 1992: d–f holotype a, d dorsal view b, e lateral view c, f frontal view g labels of holotype h abdomen i penis j tegmen, lateral view k tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–f: 0.5 mm, h: 0.2 mm, i–k: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Figs 2a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[595,618,1264,1286]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">3a</figureCitation>
)................................................................. 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1293,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1293,1315]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
- Elytra black or dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[497,570,1293,1315]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Figs 6a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[580,604,1293,1315]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">9a</figureCitation>
)................................................................... 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
2. Body oval (
<figureCitation box="[339,410,1322,1344]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 4a</figureCitation>
); abdominal postcoxal lines reaching 1/2 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1011,1084,1322,1344]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 4d</figureCitation>
); penis guide shorter than 1/2 length of parameres (
<figureCitation box="[364,429,1352,1374]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 4f</figureCitation>
)................................................................................. 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
- Body elongate oval (
<figureCitation box="[425,495,1381,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,366,1376]" captionTargetId="figure-102@5.[151,1436,345,1400]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Axinoscymnus cardilobus Ren et Pang, 1992: d–f holotype a, d dorsal view b, e lateral view c, f frontal view g labels of holotype h abdomen i penis j tegmen, lateral view k tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–f: 0.5 mm, h: 0.2 mm, i–k: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 2a</figureCitation>
); abdominal postcoxal lines reaching 3/4 length of ventrite 1 (
<figureCitation box="[1088,1159,1381,1403]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,366,1376]" captionTargetId="figure-102@5.[151,1436,345,1400]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Axinoscymnus cardilobus Ren et Pang, 1992: d–f holotype a, d dorsal view b, e lateral view c, f frontal view g labels of holotype h abdomen i penis j tegmen, lateral view k tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–f: 0.5 mm, h: 0.2 mm, i–k: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 2h</figureCitation>
); penis guide slightly shorter than parameres (
<figureCitation box="[385,449,1410,1432]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,249,1424,1448]" captionTargetBox="[168,1423,366,1376]" captionTargetId="figure-102@5.[151,1436,345,1400]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Axinoscymnus cardilobus Ren et Pang, 1992: d–f holotype a, d dorsal view b, e lateral view c, f frontal view g labels of holotype h abdomen i penis j tegmen, lateral view k tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–f: 0.5 mm, h: 0.2 mm, i–k: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 2j</figureCitation>
)................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Ren et Pang" authorityName="Ren et Pang" box="[1069,1436,1410,1432]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cardilobus">
<emphasis box="[1069,1314,1410,1432]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Axinoscymnus cardilobus</emphasis>
Ren et Pang
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
3. Body length less than 
<quantity box="[439,515,1440,1462]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="mm" value="1.6">1.6 mm</quantity>
; apex of penis broadened, knife-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[909,979,1440,1462]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 3e</figureCitation>
); parameres short and broad in inner view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1823,1847]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,861,1785]" captionTargetId="figure-286@6.[151,1436,849,1800]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 3. Axinoscymnus apioides Kuznetsov et Ren, 1991: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[226,250,1469,1491]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="g" value="3.0">3g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
)................................................................ 
<taxonomicName authority="Kuznetsov et Ren" authorityName="Kuznetsov et Ren" box="[1035,1437,1469,1490]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apioides">
<emphasis box="[1035,1259,1469,1490]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Axinoscymnus apioides</emphasis>
Kuznetsov et Ren
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
- Body length more than 
<quantity box="[458,535,1498,1520]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.9" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="mm" value="1.9">1.9 mm</quantity>
; penis slender with a pointed apex (
<figureCitation box="[889,961,1498,1520]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 4e</figureCitation>
); parameres long and narrow in inner view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1893,1917]" captionTargetBox="[171,1414,970,1850]" captionTargetId="figure-297@7.[151,1436,957,1869]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 4. Axinoscymnus gongxinensis Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.2 mm, e–g: 0.1 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
Fig. 
<quantity box="[226,251,1528,1550]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" unit="g" value="4.0">4g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
).......................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Peng et Chen" authorityName="Peng et Chen" authorityYear="2022" box="[968,1373,1528,1550]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gongxinensis" status="sp. n.">
<emphasis box="[968,1236,1528,1549]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Axinoscymnus gongxinensis</emphasis>
Peng et Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1382,1436,1528,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1382,1436,1528,1549]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" rank="species">sp. n.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1557,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1557,1579]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
4. Elytra light brown to dark brown (
<figureCitation box="[555,628,1557,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Figs 5a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[638,662,1557,1579]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="10.[151,250,1584,1608]" captionTargetBox="[170,1418,901,1548]" captionTargetId="figure-274@10.[151,1436,885,1561]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 6. Axinoscymnus singaporicus Pang et Gordon, 1986 (Paratype): a dorsal view b ventral view c lateral view d labels of paratype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">6a</figureCitation>
).............................................................. 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1586,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1586,1608]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
- Elytra black (
<figureCitation box="[355,428,1586,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1937,1961]" captionTargetBox="[172,1416,935,1899]" captionTargetId="figure-308@14.[151,1436,921,1914]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 9. Axinoscymnus hamulatus Peng et Chen, sp. n.: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Figs 9a</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[438,474,1586,1608]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1348,1372]" captionTargetBox="[173,1417,395,1316]" captionTargetId="figure-116@19.[151,1436,381,1324]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. Axinoscymnus nigripennis Kamiya, 1965: a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">12a</figureCitation>
).............................................................................. 8
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1615,1638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1615,1638]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">5. Penis slender with a pointed apex........................................................................ 6</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" box="[151,1436,1645,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead box="[151,1436,1645,1667]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">- Penis stout with a blunt apex............................................................................ 7</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
6. Elytra brown without dark markings. Penis guide widest at base in lateral view, then sharply converging to a pointed tip (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1918,1942]" captionTargetBox="[170,1424,996,1878]" captionTargetId="figure-282@8.[151,1436,987,1895]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. Axinoscymnus glotticus Ren et Pang, 1992 (Holotype): a dorsal view b lateral view c frontal view d abdomen e penis f tegmen, lateral view g tegmen, inner view h labels of holotype. Scale bars: a–c: 0.5 mm, d: 0.1 mm, e–g: 0.05 mm." pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Fig. 5f</figureCitation>
).................................................................... 
<taxonomicName authority="Ren et Pang" authorityName="Ren et Pang" box="[1088,1436,1704,1725]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glotticus">
<emphasis box="[1088,1315,1704,1725]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Axinoscymnus glotticus</emphasis>
Ren et Pang
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1264,2019]" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
<keyLead pageId="3" pageNumber="434">
- Elytra yellowish brown with dark brown markings at humeral and apical parts. Penis guide widest at base in lateral view, then gradually converging to a pointed tip.................................................. 
<taxonomicName authority="Kamiya" authorityName="Kamiya" box="[1183,1436,1762,1784]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Axinoscymnus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="434" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rai">
<emphasis box="[1183,1354,1763,1784]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="434">Axinoscymnus rai</emphasis>
Kamiya
</taxonomicName>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
